1
00:00:14,567 --> 00:00:16,300
Excuse me, where's the patient
in this room?

2
00:00:16,367 --> 00:00:18,500
- They discharged her already.
- What?

3
00:00:18,567 --> 00:00:20,433
You might still catch her
outside.

4
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:21,767
Eden, my dear!

5
00:00:21,833 --> 00:00:22,800
Eden!

6
00:00:22,867 --> 00:00:24,167
Eden, wait!

7
00:00:24,233 --> 00:00:27,467
Eden, don't leave me.

8
00:00:27,533 --> 00:00:29,100
Let me see my daughter!

9
00:00:29,167 --> 00:00:30,867
I will call the cops on Amanda

10
00:00:30,933 --> 00:00:32,100
if she doesn't stop
bothering us.

11
00:00:32,167 --> 00:00:34,333
Auntie, please,
let me talk to her.

12
00:00:34,433 --> 00:00:36,033
I'll make her understand.

13
00:00:36,100 --> 00:00:38,067
What kind of potion
did they give you?

14
00:00:38,133 --> 00:00:40,133
What kind of black magic
did they use

15
00:00:40,200 --> 00:00:43,467
to make you disrespect me
like this?

16
00:00:43,533 --> 00:00:45,133
Acceptance, Mom.

17
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:46,533
Understanding.

18
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:48,167
And care...

19
00:00:48,233 --> 00:00:50,600
that I thought I'd get from you!

20
00:00:50,667 --> 00:00:53,200
Because I've been yearning
for it for so long!

21
00:00:53,267 --> 00:00:54,833
Take Eden inside.

22
00:00:54,900 --> 00:00:55,933
How dare you!

23
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:58,567
Give me my daughter back!

24
00:00:58,633 --> 00:01:00,267
Yenyen!

25
00:01:00,333 --> 00:01:01,700
Eden!

26
00:01:01,767 --> 00:01:05,300
Let's go home! Eden!

27
00:01:05,367 --> 00:01:09,000
Don't do this to me.

28
00:01:09,100 --> 00:01:10,267
Hey guys, guys.

29
00:01:10,333 --> 00:01:11,833
Look, look, look, look.

30
00:01:11,900 --> 00:01:13,333
T-rex?

31
00:01:13,400 --> 00:01:16,467
It's not just T-rex.
It's cutiesaurus.

32
00:01:16,533 --> 00:01:18,500
So look what we got here.

33
00:02:06,467 --> 00:02:08,333
Eden is happy now.

34
00:02:09,833 --> 00:02:12,300
My daughter is happy now.

35
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:18,333
She doesn't need me anymore.

36
00:02:21,767 --> 00:02:24,233
Eden doesn't need me anymore.

37
00:02:54,633 --> 00:02:56,100
Where is that witch?

38
00:02:56,167 --> 00:02:57,700
I'm following her right now.

39
00:02:57,767 --> 00:02:59,600
She just went outof the village.

40
00:02:59,667 --> 00:03:00,933
She's walking alone.

41
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:03,200
To be fair,

42
00:03:03,267 --> 00:03:09,033
she still has strength
after all that happened.

43
00:03:09,100 --> 00:03:10,800
She's tough.

44
00:03:10,867 --> 00:03:15,133
I don't know how she can cope
after what Eden did to her.

45
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:16,300
She might go crazy.

46
00:03:16,367 --> 00:03:17,500
I don't care.

47
00:03:17,567 --> 00:03:19,400
I really don't.

48
00:03:19,467 --> 00:03:23,733
She can get hit by a car
for all I care.

49
00:03:23,833 --> 00:03:27,133
That's not enough to pay for
what she did to my family.

50
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:29,933
She's pretty tough, isn't she?

51
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:35,833
After everything I did,
I finally found her weakness.

52
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:41,367
Her very own precious Eden.

53
00:03:43,433 --> 00:03:47,633
Now I want to see how far
she can go.

54
00:03:47,700 --> 00:03:51,933
I want to drain her strength.

55
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:56,500
Until she crumbles
to the ground.

56
00:03:57,567 --> 00:04:00,167
What do you want me to do?

57
00:05:10,700 --> 00:05:12,833
Amanda.

58
00:05:18,333 --> 00:05:19,833
You beast!

59
00:05:19,900 --> 00:05:21,133
Pig!

60
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:23,100
- Oh, really?
- You and your sister are pigs.

61
00:05:23,167 --> 00:05:24,900
You're calling me a pig?

62
00:05:24,967 --> 00:05:28,133
A pig?

63
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:30,000
Really? Are you hungry?

64
00:05:30,067 --> 00:05:32,533
Here. Have some food.

65
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:36,167
Go on, eat! Eat that!

66
00:05:40,567 --> 00:05:42,433
Emma, thank you.

67
00:05:45,933 --> 00:05:50,300
Red, how's Eden?

68
00:05:50,367 --> 00:05:51,800
She's okay.

69
00:05:51,867 --> 00:05:53,800
She's getting some rest.

70
00:05:55,700 --> 00:05:57,667
She's in a very complicated
situation.

71
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:02,633
I can't imagine what
she's going through.

72
00:06:04,100 --> 00:06:09,600
You know, honestly, even though
I really hate her mom...

73
00:06:09,700 --> 00:06:13,967
I can't help but feel sorry
for her.

74
00:06:16,367 --> 00:06:18,167
Eden needs you now, Red.

75
00:06:18,233 --> 00:06:21,833
So try to give her all
the support she needs.

76
00:06:23,767 --> 00:06:25,600
I will, Dad. Thank you.

77
00:06:27,433 --> 00:06:30,633
By the way, have you seen
your mom?

78
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:32,167
No. Why?

79
00:06:32,233 --> 00:06:34,400
I've been looking for her.

80
00:06:37,133 --> 00:06:42,233
Sir, Ma'am Rina left
with Sir Zandro.

81
00:06:42,333 --> 00:06:44,800
At this time?

82
00:06:44,867 --> 00:06:46,767
I wonder where they went.

83
00:06:48,667 --> 00:06:50,133
Here's more!

84
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:51,100
Here!

85
00:06:51,167 --> 00:06:52,333
What do you want from me?

86
00:06:52,400 --> 00:06:54,533
Why did you bring me here?

87
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:57,400
Surprise, surprise, Amanda.

88
00:06:57,467 --> 00:06:58,633
I wasn't surprised.

89
00:06:58,700 --> 00:07:00,700
I know you're behind all
of this.

90
00:07:00,767 --> 00:07:03,400
I'm glad you know that.

91
00:07:03,467 --> 00:07:07,767
I just want to see you
for the last time,

92
00:07:07,833 --> 00:07:09,300
looking like this.

93
00:07:09,367 --> 00:07:13,433
You look so gross and pitiful.

94
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:15,667
No one's on your side.

95
00:07:15,767 --> 00:07:16,767
You're evil!

96
00:07:16,833 --> 00:07:18,533
What a pitiful person.

97
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:19,967
- You're shameless!
- You're calling me shameless?

98
00:07:20,033 --> 00:07:23,200
Yes. Let me go. I'm going
to get you back!

99
00:07:23,267 --> 00:07:26,033
You'll get me back? Why?

100
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:27,133
What are you capable of doing?

101
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:28,333
Look at yourself.

102
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:29,467
What can you do? What?

103
00:07:29,533 --> 00:07:30,533
Let me go!

104
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:33,600
Fight me fair and square!

105
00:07:33,667 --> 00:07:35,467
Why would I do that?

106
00:07:35,533 --> 00:07:36,767
You can't because
you're a coward!

107
00:07:36,833 --> 00:07:37,933
Oh, you're calling me a coward?

108
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,767
Who's tied up right now?

109
00:07:39,833 --> 00:07:40,867
Because you're a coward!

110
00:07:40,933 --> 00:07:43,967
Both of you! You're ganging up
on me!

111
00:07:44,033 --> 00:07:47,100
You are nothing but
a piece of junk,

112
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:49,600
just like the rest
of the garbage here!

113
00:07:49,667 --> 00:07:50,833
You're evil!

114
00:07:50,900 --> 00:07:55,167
- I know! But I'm good at it!
- Oh, really?

115
00:07:55,233 --> 00:07:57,033
You took my daughter
away from me!

116
00:07:57,100 --> 00:07:59,233
Because you started it!

117
00:07:59,300 --> 00:08:02,100
You took my son from me,
you and your lover!

118
00:08:02,167 --> 00:08:03,400
I had nothing to do
with his death!

119
00:08:03,467 --> 00:08:05,233
But you're still insisting
I did!

120
00:08:05,300 --> 00:08:06,867
You shouldn't have gotten
my daughter involved!

121
00:08:06,933 --> 00:08:08,633
You poisoned her mind!

122
00:08:08,700 --> 00:08:11,333
What do you mean I poisoned
her mind?

123
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:13,233
I didn't do that!

124
00:08:13,300 --> 00:08:15,400
She made the decision
to stay away from you.

125
00:08:15,467 --> 00:08:16,967
Do you know why?

126
00:08:17,033 --> 00:08:19,967
Because you're worthless.

127
00:08:20,033 --> 00:08:21,633
You're nothing, Amanda!

128
00:08:21,733 --> 00:08:23,133
That's not true!

129
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:25,533
I know you won't believe me.

130
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:28,333
That's why I brought proof
for you to see.

131
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:31,433
Here, watch this.

132
00:08:31,500 --> 00:08:33,233
I've made my decision, Auntie.

133
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:37,333
I don't want to see
my mom anymore.

134
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:45,367
It hurts, but I'm doing
this for our own good.

135
00:08:48,733 --> 00:08:51,833
So now tell me...

136
00:08:51,900 --> 00:08:57,067
How does it feel to get
disowned by your own daughter?

137
00:08:57,167 --> 00:08:59,767
How does it feel to get cut off

138
00:08:59,833 --> 00:09:03,100
by your own flesh and blood,
Amanda?

139
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:05,000
Why?

140
00:09:05,067 --> 00:09:06,633
Why?

141
00:09:06,700 --> 00:09:09,467
You're asking me why?

142
00:09:09,533 --> 00:09:11,567
Look at yourself, Amanda!

143
00:09:11,633 --> 00:09:13,967
What kind of a person are you?
You're a worthless mother!

144
00:09:14,033 --> 00:09:17,633
A worthless human being!

145
00:09:17,700 --> 00:09:19,467
You're not going anywhere!

146
00:09:19,533 --> 00:09:21,667
I have an instant shield.

147
00:09:21,733 --> 00:09:23,033
What about you?
What do you have?

148
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:24,367
You have nothing.

149
00:09:24,433 --> 00:09:28,033
You don't have anything!

150
00:09:28,133 --> 00:09:31,467
What? Do you still want
to fight me?

151
00:09:31,533 --> 00:09:33,733
Just kill me!

152
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:36,300
I don't give a damn
if you kill me!

153
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:38,100
No, no, no, Amanda.

154
00:09:38,167 --> 00:09:41,733
Because death is such
an easy escape.

155
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:49,100
I want you to suffer
from my revenge!

156
00:09:49,167 --> 00:09:51,167
I have your daughter.

157
00:09:51,233 --> 00:09:53,300
She's all mine.

158
00:09:53,367 --> 00:09:55,533
Zandro, you know what to do.

159
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:56,633
Yes, Rina.

160
00:09:56,700 --> 00:09:58,667
Your daughter is mine now.

161
00:09:58,733 --> 00:10:01,200
I haven't worked out in a while.

162
00:10:15,167 --> 00:10:16,200
What now?

163
00:10:16,267 --> 00:10:19,133
Come on, fight me! It's boring
to spar with you!

164
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:22,400
You're not a man! You're gay!

165
00:10:22,467 --> 00:10:25,500
Luckily, I'm a gentleman.

166
00:10:36,867 --> 00:10:39,100
Eden!

167
00:10:52,033 --> 00:10:53,600
Carry her, Zandro.

168
00:11:08,300 --> 00:11:09,700
Go straight ahead.

169
00:11:22,567 --> 00:11:24,633
Good job, Zandro.

170
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:30,300
This is it, Amanda.

171
00:11:30,367 --> 00:11:34,100
This will be your new home.

172
00:11:34,167 --> 00:11:35,233
What do you want me to do?

173
00:11:35,300 --> 00:11:37,533
Do you want me to kill her?

174
00:11:39,133 --> 00:11:42,233
I'm begging you, just kill me.

175
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:46,500
My daughter abandoned me.

176
00:11:46,567 --> 00:11:50,233
She's gone.

177
00:11:50,300 --> 00:11:53,133
I don't have a reason
to live anymore.

178
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:55,667
Just kill me to put an end
to this.

179
00:11:55,733 --> 00:11:57,433
I'm begging you.

180
00:11:57,500 --> 00:12:00,567
Amanda, didn't I tell you
already?

181
00:12:00,633 --> 00:12:04,600
Death is just too easy!

182
00:12:04,667 --> 00:12:09,433
That's not what I want for you!

183
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:15,000
I want you to suffer longer.

184
00:12:15,100 --> 00:12:18,133
Because as long as I have
your daughter,

185
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:25,567
I'll make sure that you'll
suffer, Amanda.

186
00:12:25,633 --> 00:12:28,900
Just kill me to end all this.

187
00:12:28,967 --> 00:12:31,567
No, I'm sorry, Amanda.

188
00:12:31,633 --> 00:12:36,167
Request denied!

189
00:12:42,900 --> 00:12:45,500
Job well done.

190
00:14:30,300 --> 00:14:32,900
Mom!

191
00:14:32,967 --> 00:14:34,067
Yen...

192
00:14:34,133 --> 00:14:36,333
Yen, what's wrong?

193
00:14:36,400 --> 00:14:39,733
I had a dream that my mom
was in danger.

194
00:14:39,800 --> 00:14:41,633
She needs help.

195
00:15:18,300 --> 00:15:19,767
Red, why is it like that?

196
00:15:19,833 --> 00:15:22,833
My dream seemed so real.

197
00:15:22,900 --> 00:15:23,967
Just calm down, okay?

198
00:15:24,033 --> 00:15:25,600
Drink some water first.

199
00:15:29,067 --> 00:15:30,233
I'm worried about you.

200
00:15:30,300 --> 00:15:33,500
Something might happen
to our baby.

201
00:15:33,567 --> 00:15:35,200
I'm okay.

202
00:15:37,800 --> 00:15:42,233
I'm just so affected from my
dream earlier.

203
00:15:42,300 --> 00:15:47,033
I dreamed my mom
was suffering.

204
00:15:47,100 --> 00:15:50,700
She was in a dark place.
I heard her scream.

205
00:15:50,767 --> 00:15:53,733
As if she was inside a well.

206
00:15:53,800 --> 00:15:56,867
Red, what if something
bad happened to my mom?

207
00:15:56,933 --> 00:15:58,200
Yen, what are you talking about?

208
00:15:58,267 --> 00:16:02,500
It's just a dream.
Don't think like that.

209
00:16:02,567 --> 00:16:09,500
My mom put my life and
our baby's life at risk.

210
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:11,167
But I can't abandon her.

211
00:16:11,233 --> 00:16:12,900
She's still my mom.

212
00:16:16,033 --> 00:16:18,633
Yen, I know.

213
00:16:18,700 --> 00:16:20,767
But you can't stress yourself
right now.

214
00:16:20,833 --> 00:16:23,433
It won't do you any good.

215
00:16:23,500 --> 00:16:28,167
You need to recover
for our baby.

216
00:16:28,233 --> 00:16:30,467
I'm sure she's sad.

217
00:16:30,533 --> 00:16:37,033
Who wouldn't be sad
after what happened?

218
00:16:37,100 --> 00:16:39,733
Come on, let's go back to sleep.

219
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:41,067
Stop thinking about it.

220
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,633
Can you...

221
00:17:56,533 --> 00:17:59,567
Can you help me?

222
00:17:59,633 --> 00:18:02,033
What can I do for you?

223
00:18:02,100 --> 00:18:03,667
Where am I?

224
00:18:03,733 --> 00:18:05,367
You're on earth.

225
00:18:05,433 --> 00:18:06,467
Why do you look like that?

226
00:18:06,533 --> 00:18:09,367
I think she's crazy.

227
00:18:09,433 --> 00:18:12,867
My daughter.

228
00:18:12,933 --> 00:18:16,967
My daughter. She doesn't
love me anymore.

229
00:18:17,033 --> 00:18:19,767
Maybe you're a bad mother.

230
00:18:19,833 --> 00:18:21,200
No!

231
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:23,100
I'm not a bad mother!

232
00:18:23,167 --> 00:18:25,533
They are bad people! Not me!

233
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:26,933
That's not true.

234
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:28,867
Fine! Can you please leave?

235
00:18:28,933 --> 00:18:30,300
You stink! Go!

236
00:18:30,367 --> 00:18:32,700
Let's get out of here.

237
00:18:55,700 --> 00:18:56,833
Mom?

238
00:18:58,667 --> 00:19:00,500
Mom?

239
00:19:00,567 --> 00:19:03,133
Mom?

240
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:07,233
Mom?

241
00:19:07,300 --> 00:19:08,900
Yenyen?

242
00:19:08,967 --> 00:19:15,500
Yenyen?

243
00:19:15,567 --> 00:19:16,733
Thank God you came back.

244
00:19:16,800 --> 00:19:18,633
Thank you for coming back
for me.

245
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:22,100
Yenyen. I love you so much.

246
00:19:22,167 --> 00:19:24,433
Hey! You crazy woman!
Let go of my daughter!

247
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:26,767
Let go of her! Give her to me!

248
00:19:26,833 --> 00:19:28,433
That's my daughter! Let her go!

249
00:19:28,533 --> 00:19:29,567
You?

250
00:19:29,633 --> 00:19:30,800
Let my daughter go!

251
00:19:30,867 --> 00:19:32,967
You're always hurting me!

252
00:19:33,033 --> 00:19:35,267
You and your brother!

253
00:19:35,333 --> 00:19:36,567
You bastard!

254
00:19:36,633 --> 00:19:38,533
You won't leave us alone!

255
00:19:38,600 --> 00:19:40,967
- You ruined our lives!
- Let me go!

256
00:19:41,033 --> 00:19:44,067
- You're evil!
- You're crazy!

257
00:19:44,133 --> 00:19:46,500
Rina!

258
00:19:46,567 --> 00:19:49,133
Stop it! Let go of her!

259
00:19:49,200 --> 00:19:53,733
Crazy woman! Crazy!

260
00:19:53,800 --> 00:19:56,167
Don't let her get away!

261
00:20:03,233 --> 00:20:06,800
Are you okay back there, Eden?

262
00:20:06,867 --> 00:20:08,233
I'm okay, Auntie.

263
00:20:10,867 --> 00:20:12,500
Why are you looking around?

264
00:20:14,967 --> 00:20:17,833
Are you hoping to see your mom?

265
00:20:20,967 --> 00:20:22,133
Come on, Eden.

266
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:29,033
Let me just remind you
what your mom did to you.

267
00:20:29,100 --> 00:20:30,900
I know it's hard.

268
00:20:30,967 --> 00:20:33,000
It's hard to forget.

269
00:20:33,067 --> 00:20:35,600
It's hard to disown her.

270
00:20:35,700 --> 00:20:38,567
Because she's your mom.

271
00:20:38,633 --> 00:20:41,200
But, my God, I think it's time
for you to think

272
00:20:41,267 --> 00:20:43,567
about your child.

273
00:20:43,633 --> 00:20:45,533
Sorry, Auntie.

274
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:49,633
I can't help myself
but think about her.

275
00:20:49,700 --> 00:20:52,000
I'm still worried about my mom.

276
00:20:52,067 --> 00:20:56,767
I don't think she wanted me
to lose the baby.

277
00:20:56,833 --> 00:20:58,800
Listen to me, Eden.

278
00:21:01,100 --> 00:21:04,767
She hates my family.

279
00:21:04,833 --> 00:21:07,167
Our family.

280
00:21:07,233 --> 00:21:09,533
She doesn't like Red.

281
00:21:09,633 --> 00:21:13,300
Do you think she'll love
that child?

282
00:21:13,367 --> 00:21:15,933
Your child is carrying
our blood.

283
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:18,100
She hates that child!

284
00:21:21,467 --> 00:21:24,767
God forgive me, but I'd rather
see you lose that child.

285
00:21:24,833 --> 00:21:30,567
I don't want to see the result
of your biggest mistake!

286
00:21:35,233 --> 00:21:38,767
Mom, mom, please.

287
00:21:38,833 --> 00:21:41,667
Don't stress her out.

288
00:21:41,767 --> 00:21:45,567
Can we just leave her be
for now?

289
00:21:45,633 --> 00:21:47,300
She's still going through
the healing process.

290
00:21:47,367 --> 00:21:53,200
Look, I just want her
to know the truth.

291
00:21:53,267 --> 00:21:56,900
I mean, you're looking
for your mom.

292
00:21:56,967 --> 00:21:57,900
You're looking for Amanda.

293
00:21:57,967 --> 00:22:01,467
But is she looking for you?

294
00:22:01,533 --> 00:22:03,133
I don't think so.

295
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:04,933
Several days had passed.

296
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:07,267
Your mom should be
looking for you

297
00:22:07,333 --> 00:22:08,933
if she is concerned about you.

298
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:10,167
Does she care about you?

299
00:22:10,233 --> 00:22:12,300
Does she care about your child?

300
00:22:12,367 --> 00:22:15,667
No, she's not!

301
00:22:15,767 --> 00:22:18,233
My God!

302
00:22:18,300 --> 00:22:22,367
It's the first time I've met
someone like her.

303
00:22:22,433 --> 00:22:25,767
She's so...

304
00:22:25,833 --> 00:22:27,233
selfish.

305
00:22:29,067 --> 00:22:32,867
She only thinks about herself
instead of you.

306
00:22:32,933 --> 00:22:35,367
I mean, look at me.

307
00:22:35,433 --> 00:22:38,533
I admit, Eden.

308
00:22:38,600 --> 00:22:40,667
I didn't like you at first.

309
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:48,067
But because I'm a mom,
I accepted you.

310
00:22:50,767 --> 00:22:55,000
That is motherly love.

311
00:22:55,067 --> 00:22:56,833
Unconditional love.

312
00:22:59,433 --> 00:23:04,467
Once you become a mother,

313
00:23:04,533 --> 00:23:07,167
you will understand what
unconditional love is.

314
00:23:07,233 --> 00:23:09,367
Motherly love.

315
00:23:09,433 --> 00:23:12,667
It's a sacrificial love.

316
00:23:14,433 --> 00:23:16,700
Something that Amanda
is not capable of.

317
00:24:38,100 --> 00:24:40,200
What's this?

318
00:24:41,267 --> 00:24:42,800
Don't get out of the car.

319
00:24:42,867 --> 00:24:46,000
Miss, are you okay?

320
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:05,800
You are lucky, Eden, to always
have Red by your side.

321
00:25:05,867 --> 00:25:06,900
Oh, that's true.

322
00:25:06,967 --> 00:25:08,633
Indeed, Doctor.

323
00:25:08,700 --> 00:25:10,800
She's very lucky to have us.

324
00:25:10,867 --> 00:25:12,800
Thank you, Auntie.

325
00:25:12,867 --> 00:25:14,867
I owe you everything.

326
00:25:14,933 --> 00:25:16,033
I told you.

327
00:25:16,100 --> 00:25:19,933
I am better than your mother.

328
00:25:20,000 --> 00:25:24,000
I know that she didn't mean
to hurt me.

329
00:25:24,067 --> 00:25:25,400
Of course.

330
00:25:25,467 --> 00:25:28,967
Because you are her life.

331
00:25:29,033 --> 00:25:32,167
Just like how you are
to your child.

332
00:25:32,233 --> 00:25:40,167
I hope you understand where
your mom is coming from.

333
00:25:40,267 --> 00:25:43,300
I wish I could see her,
so we can talk.

334
00:25:43,367 --> 00:25:45,600
I hope she's okay.

335
00:25:45,667 --> 00:25:46,600
Where have you been?

336
00:25:46,667 --> 00:25:48,867
I just picked this up.

337
00:25:48,933 --> 00:25:50,767
You got to be kidding me.

338
00:25:50,833 --> 00:25:53,433
Are you proposing to Eden?
